    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Decapeptide-25 SP Amide Maleate is the maleic acid salt of a single chain human peptide produced synthetically to be identical to a portion of the protein, Type I Cuticular Ha4 Keratin, and contains 10 amino acids consisting of arginine, glutamic acid, glutamine, glycine, leucine and lysine in which the C-terminus is an amide. The parent protein contains a maximum of 436 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
